Can anyone help with this nightmare?
text: The hospital bills racked up by my Stepdad before he died were just under $450k. The hospital placed a lien against his estate for this entire amount. I called 2 different attorneys, and both said that this was legal, and neither of them believed that they could get the payoff balance reduced by more than 50%, and 50% would be the very best. There must be a better solution out there. I welcome all suggestions please.
